HEADWORD: Ludlow group
<hw>Lud"low group`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>A subdivision of the British Upper Silurian lying below the Old Red
Sandstone; -- so named from the <etsep>Ludlow</etsep>, in Western
England. See the <xex>Chart</xex> of <er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ludwigite</ent>⟦br⟧
